    {
      "id": "CC-1984-07",
      "cipher_system": "Periodic Polyalphabetic",
      "raw": "UKHCY TGYVH GWMFG BIENN OQPVO WKFUY GZLRF WXGXF SENIY GLPBM HGVWF VOFWF WYGAS MFSAV OZUKW ZZZYF BRFNT XSKKE YNTXX VLRJH GWYMU BUHUY JETRF GVGJR OWMNV WRTUL KXBZY ZUGNI AVEVL MQVEQ GRAMF ZANNC UKHCY TGYVG WPVZW ZOGLK XAXYU GRZAN NCUKK ZUWEP RWBKX YITVI KKYYX V",
      "hints": [
        {
          "text": "To end this issue, here is a cryptogram by Warren t. McCready which appeared in the July-August 1983 issue of The Cryptogram.  It is a period 8 cipher using the same keyword alphabet for both pt and ct.  When the tip is placed, the partial tableau illustrated is pbtained.  The reader is invited to complete the tableau, and read the message which, incidentally, is in very easy Spanish."
        },
        {
          "text": "nero han hecho progresar considerable"
        }
      ],
